comments: From 1972 onwards Elvis incorporated the spiritual "Amen" into his live performances of "I Got a Woman". Though "Amen" is not listed anywhere on the album, this is the first commercial release of one of these performances. The "Amen" section is highlighted by vocalist J.D. Sumner of The Stamps Quartet demonstrating the range of his bass voice.
